I just want to relate to my fellow counselors that I did say that when we talked last meeting, folks wanted them to come before the public meeting. And the other thing here is that the charter provision is a majority of us can reject. And if we do not unduly, we can't unduly reject and it has to be within 30 days. So, there's some time clocks here. If we wait two weeks and say, you know, please submit everything, I think we're within the time clock. It's really untested and we don't have legal.

